[[File:BellicoseFighterWing-VaderDarkVisions2.png|thumb|280px|[[Bellicose's fighter wing|An Imperial fighter wing]] from the [[Bellicose (Imperial-class)|''Bellicose'']]]]
A '''fighter wing''', also referred to as an '''attack wing''', '''flight wing''', or simply a '''wing''' was an organizational unit of [[starfighter]]s used in various [[Navy|navies]] or [[fleet]]s.

==Description==
===Overview===
A [[Starfighter|fighter]] wing,<ref name="Before the Awakening">''[[Before the Awakening]]''</ref> also referred to as an attack wing<ref name="TIE Fighter Model">''[[Star Wars: TIE Fighter Deluxe Book and Model Set]]''</ref> or flight wing,<ref name="MF 81">[[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon 81|''Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon'' 81]]</ref> was an organizational type of military unit of [[starfighter]]s.<ref name="Before the Awakening">''[[Before the Awakening]]''</ref> Varying [[Navy|navies]] and [[fleet]]s deployed fighter wings.<ref name="AND">[[A New Dawn (novel)|''A New Dawn'']]</ref> After studying [[Imperial Military]] history, [[Eli N. Vanto|Eli Vanto]] came to know that in melee battles, a fighter wing or two could make the difference between victory and destruction.<ref name="Thrawn: Treason">''[[Thrawn: Treason]]''</ref> The commanding officer of a fighter wing was typically designated as a [[Wing Commander|wing commander]].<ref name="LCZA">{{InsiderCite|156|Last Call at the Zero Angle}}</ref>

===Alliance to Restore the Republic===
{{Quote|All wings report in.|Garven Dreis|<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|VI}}</ref>}}
The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]] deployed fighter wings while active, which could be headquartered in a military base,<ref name="Darth Vader 14">[[Darth Vader (2015) 14|''Darth Vader'' (2015) 14]]</ref> with its commanding officer known as a wing [[commander]].<ref name="CVD New">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref> Large [[squadron]]s were also occasionally referred to as wings.<ref name="Episode VI">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

===Confederacy of Independent Systems===
The [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Separatist Alliance's]] [[Confederacy military|armed forces]] utilized fighter wings, which they designated as flight wings, during their history. Separatist [[Hyena-class Droid Fighter/Bomber|''Hyena''-class Droid Bombers]] were deployed to flight wings throughout [[the galaxy]] after production was increased.<ref name="MF 81" />

===First Order===
The [[First Order]] used fighter wings in their [[First Order military|armed forces]]. First Order [[Resurgent-class Star Destroyer|''Resurgent''-class Star Destroyers]] were equipped with two fighter wings<ref name="TFA VD">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref> that were composed of [[TIE/fo space superiority fighter]]s, [[TIE/sf space superiority fighter]]s,<ref name="Episode VII">{{Film|VII}}</ref> and [[TIE/se Bomber]]s.<ref name="Allegiance">[[Allegiance 1|''Allegiance'' 1]]</ref>

===Galactic Empire===
{{Quote|Get the crews to their fighters.|Darth Vader|<ref name="Episode IV" />}}
A full attack wing within the [[Galactic Empire]] consisted of six [[squadron]]s, which numbered to seventy-two ships&mdash;usually forty-eight [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter]]s, twelve [[TIE/sa tactical bomber|TIE/sa bombers]], and twelve [[TIE/IN interceptor|TIE/in interceptors]]. Imperial [[capital ship]]s carried varying numbers of fighter wings as part of their complement. [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyers]] carried one full attack wing,<ref name="TIE models set">''[[Star Wars: TIE Fighter Deluxe Book and Model Set]]''</ref> at a minimum.<ref name="SW EOSAOV">[[Star Wars Encyclopedia of Starfighters and Other Vehicles]]</ref> The [[Secutor-class Star Destroyer|''Secutor''-class Star Destroyer]] carried two fighter wings, supplementing its role as a [[carrier]].<ref name="Starships and Speeders">''[[Starships and Speeders]]''</ref> [[Imperial escort carrier]]s had a complement of one fighter wing.<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref>

When part of a ship's complement, the fighter wing fell under the command of the ship's [[commanding officer]].<ref name="Dark Visions 2">[[Vader - Dark Visions 2|''Vader - Dark Visions'' 2]]</ref> Fighter wings also acted as part of a [[planet]]ary defense force.<ref name="Forged in Battle">''[[Forged in Battle]]''</ref> Additionally, Imperial fighter wings could act as independent military units that were headquartered on a [[starship]], rather than serve solely as the ship's complement. These fighter wings were led by a [[colonel]], and were supported by a [[major]].<ref name="Alphabet Squadron">[[Alphabet Squadron (novel)|''Alphabet Squadron'']]</ref> The leader of a fighter wing within the Empire was identified as a wing commander.<ref name="LCZA" />

===Galactic Republic===
The size of a fighter wing of the [[Galactic Republic]] varied, as one fighter wing could be composed of 120 starfighters<ref name="Lead by Example">''[[Lead by Example]]''</ref> while four fighter wings could contain 400 starfighters. ''Venator''-class [[Star Destroyer]]s, had the ability to carry four full fighter wings.<ref name="Rise">''[[Rise of the Separatists]]''</ref> The [[Maelstrom-class battle cruiser|''Maelstrom''-class battle cruiser]] carried one fighter wing, which could contain up to 120 starfighters, though it also carried ninety-six.<ref name="Lead by Example" /> Wing commanders served as the commanding officers of fighter wings.<ref name="Citadel Rescue">{{TCW|Citadel Rescue}}</ref>

===New Republic and Resistance===
The [[Nebulon-C escort frigate]] used by the [[New Republic]] and the [[Resistance]] could carry one fighter wing.<ref name="TLJ ICS">''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref> Wing commander or wing leader was used to identify the commanding [[officer]]s of fighter wings in the New Republic and the Resistance.<ref name="SW 177">[[Star Wars Insider 177|''Star Wars Insider'' 177]]</ref> A New Republic [[Deliverance's starfighter wing|fighter wing]] led by [[Commander]] [[Wyl Lark]] was stationed on the [[Star Destroyer]] ''[[Deliverance]]'' and consisted of [[Flare Squadron]], [[Hail Squadron]], and [[Wild Squadron]].<ref name="Victory's Price">''[[Victory's Price: An Alphabet Squadron Novel]]''</ref>

===Vak Combine===
The [[Vak Combine]], a government within the [[Unknown Regions]] of [[the galaxy]], utilized fighter wings. The military formation was known to the [[Chiss Ascendancy]], another faction in the region.<ref name="Chaos Rising">''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Chaos Rising]]''</ref>

==History==
===During the Clone Wars===
By the start of the [[Clone Wars]] between the Galactic Republic and the Separatist Alliance, fighter wings were deployed by both the [[Republic Navy]] and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems Navy|Confederacy navy]]. ''Venator''-class [[Star]] [[Destroyer]]s were each equipped with four fighter wings, which they utilized throughout their service.<ref name="Rise" /> Early in the war, following the [[Battle of Christophsis]], the Separatists witnessed the success of their ''Hyena''-class [[bomber]]s, resulting in an increase in production. Shortly afterwards, ''Hyena''-class bombers appeared in Separatist flight wings across the galaxy.<ref name="MF 81" /> During the [[Battle of Lola Sayu]], [[Jedi General]]s [[Adi Gallia]] and [[Kit Fisto]] served as Wing Commanders, and led starfighter forces of a [[Lola Sayu task force|Republic task force]] against the [[Lola Sayu defense fleet|Separatist defense fleet]] that protected [[Lola Sayu]].<ref name="Citadel Rescue" />

Concurrently with the Clone Wars, shortly prior to an engagement above [[Primea]] between the [[Chiss]] Ascendancy against the [[Vak]] Combine and the [[Lioaoin Regime]], Chiss [[Admiral]] [[Ar'alani]] noted that several wings of [[Patrol ship|Vak fighters]] were not as provocative as full-class [[warship]]s and that they did not want to escalate the conflict.<ref name="Chaos Rising" />

===During the Imperial Era===
During the [[Imperial Era]], which saw the rise of rebellious activity and the [[Galactic Civil War]], both the Galactic Empire<ref name="Forged in Battle" /> and the Rebel Alliance deployed fighter wings.<ref name="Darth Vader 14" /> On [[Cymoon 1]], scores of fighter wings protected the important Imperial [[Weapons Factory Alpha]] in concert with a [[Cymoon regiment|full regiment]] and a [[Cymoon system battle group|system battle group]] in orbit. Due to the various number of ad hoc groups, however, efficacy was reduced due to communications breakdowns between the units.<ref name="Forged in Battle" /> Imperial Star Destroyers were each equipped with one fighter wing, and [[Bellicose's fighter wing|one fighter wing]] was stationed on the [[Imperial II-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial II''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Bellicose (Imperial-class)|''Bellicose'']]. The fighter wing served as the ship's complement, and included [[Beta Squadron]]. The entire fighter wing was lost due to the recklessness of the ship's commander, [[Tylux]], though the ''Bellicose'' was soon destroyed as well.<ref name="Dark Visions 2" /> During the [[Battle of Vrogas Vas]], the Rebel Alliance [[Amber Wing]] was stationed at the [[Rebel Refueling Base]] and was annihilated by [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]].<ref name="Darth Vader 14" /> Many fighter wings served within [[Death Squadron]], and participated in the [[Battle of Mako-Ta]].<ref name="SW 53">[[Star Wars (2015) 53|''Star Wars'' (2015) 53]]</ref> The ''[[Ultima II]]'' launched a [[Unidentified fighter wing (Ultima II)|fighter wing]] during the [[Battle of Ab Dalis]], though Imperial forces were defeated.<ref name="SW 15 2020">[[Star Wars (2020) 15|''Star Wars'' (2020) 15]]</ref>

The [[181st Imperial Fighter Wing]] was deployed by the Galactic Empire, and was known for the [[Color|red]] stripes that adorned their fighters. This menacing display inspired other Imperial squadrons to adopt similar designs.<ref name="Squadrons">''[[Star Wars: Squadrons]]''</ref> Another unit was the famed elite [[204th Imperial Fighter Wing]], also known as "Shadow Wing." The 204th was led by Colonel [[Shakara Nuress]]. It consisted of [[Squadron Two (Shadow Wing)|Squadron Two]], [[Squadron Three (Shadow Wing)|Squadron Three]], [[Squadron Four (Shadow Wing)|Squadron Four]], [[Squadron Five (Shadow Wing)|Squadron Five]], [[Squadron Six]], and another squadron.<ref name="Shadow Fall">''[[Shadow Fall: An Alphabet Squadron Novel]]''</ref> After the [[Battle of Endor]], the New Republic [[Hunt for Shadow Wing|hunted]] the 204th, as it was considered a deadly threat to Republic operations.<ref name="Alphabet Squadron" />

===During the New Republic Era===
Following the Galactic Civil War during the [[New Republic Era]] and the [[Cold War]], the New Republic utilized fighter wings,<ref name="Before the Awakening" /> with [[Commander]] [[Poe Dameron]] serving as a wing commander.<ref name="SW 177" /> The Resistance, a private military force with roots to the New Republic and the dissolved Rebel Alliance,<ref name="TFA VD" /> also utilized the position of wing commander,<ref name="SW 177" /> and one of its ships, the [[Anodyne (Nebulon-C)|''Anodyne'']], was equipped with one fighter wing.<ref name="TLJ ICS" /> Conversely, the First Order also deployed fighter wings, with two serving as the complement of their ''Resurgent''-class [[Battlecruiser]]s.<ref name="TFA VD" />

